values:
Well, I'm trying to figure out the person that heeps posting rather rude things on my LJ. I'm beginning to think it's Sara, but how did she get the name of my account? I could be somebody on AIM who hates me. Well, I'm pretty curious, so yeah. I don't really find it insulting as I do amusing.

Well, I went to Noah's Ark today and it was SO MUCH FUN. But I'm burnt to a crisp, despite reappyling sunblock every fifteen minutes. So yeah.

Well, today was rather uneventful. Went to the library and took stuff down for Lynn, then drove to my aunt's to see my cousin's engagement ring and talk. Then home and computer. Later my dad forced me to go out driving later. Meh.

But Sara just called and I get to go to Noah's Ark with them! <3<3 -rolls-

So I be happy.

Well, I'm back. Thank GOD. Anyway, today was a day of doing absolutely nothing. Wow. How exciting. 
Yesterday someone called me a 'stupid bitch' on one of my LJ posts. They didn't spell 'damn' correctly. I found it amusing, actually. XD

So yeah. Going to my geek job at the library tomorrow, staying as long as possible, then I'll probably call Sara. 

So yeah.

Well, I'm being dragged off to Chocago again tomorrow. The reason? My alchoholic aunt is in the hospital with 10% of her liver left. It's enough to live on, if she would -sober up-. But alchoholism is an illness. She can't help it anymore. She doesn't have anything that motivates her to stop. 

So, yeah. I might possibly have internet access, just not AIM. So, if you wanna talk, comment on here and I'll give you my e-mail addy. 

It's gonna be a loooooooong three days.

I don't like driving. At all I don't like being in control of 2000 lbs of steel. I don't like 'having contol'. I don't like the other cars, trucks, etc. I don't like narrow roads. I especially dislike turning.

Yes I'm kind of being forced to get my liscence.

Damnit.

Okay. I only get allergies at night. ONLY at night. Agh, it's so weird! And a pain in the butt. On and my face is peeling from sunburn again. That's not too unusual for me, though. Meh.

Sara and Danielle are so fricking awesome XD.

Wheeeee, I'm so tired. XD I got mineral water today that tastes like watered-down cool aid, but for some reason I like it anyway. XD

I should tidy up my room. Um. Nah, maybe not. 
I could probably go to sleep right now. I'm still recovering from the never-ending party at Lolo's. It was -so fun omg-.

Too bad I won't see her again until Fall sometime. :/

1. Reply with your name and I'll respond with something random about you.
2. I'll tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.
3. I'll pick a flavor of jello to wrestle with you in.
4. I'll say something that only makes sense to you and me.
5. I'll tell you my first memory of you.
6. I'll tell you what animal you remind me of.
7. I'll ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your journal.

Whoo.

Oh,

apparently there's an Anal Sex Month. Okay, WTFmate? XD;

Well, it's time for me to sit in front of my geek box and make another update on this here LJ. Chicago=Fun. Yeah. And stuff.

Ok. So I'm not exactly awake right now. Rah.

I have another crush on someone. Lolo= if you read this, sorry. I'm not going to say who, just because I don't want to yet. No, it's not David again. I was over David a while ago.

So yeah. Maybe I'll make a more intelligent update in the morning. 

Riiiiight.

Whoo. Going to Chicago until Monday. I'm guessing I'll have to drive part of the way there. Damn. ><;

But it should be fun! I getta see Lolo and my friends down there, and Jimmy, and of course, my other relatives. But yeah. I love travelling. XD I don't know why.

Well, today royally sucked. :D I get up this morning, and before I know it, I'm being whisked off to this hospital where my aunt Ruth is staying. She has a brain aneurysm. What fun. So they're operating tomorrow. She doesn't look very good. Since I went to the hospital today, I'm not going tomorrow. It's been a looooong day, and I'm really, really worried, but I can't do the hospital thing again tomorrow. I feel bad for not going, but :/

And then we get home, and Gramps left this hugeass message on our answering machine. Apparently my other Aunt, Tammy, is in the hospital because of seizures. Aunt Tammy is drinking herself into the grave, though. So she goes into the hospital every other month. She's making Gramps age so much, though. He's so worried.
My mom and I were giddy-happy later when we got home because we were crying and stuff all day. And we were talking.
Mom: Well, things always seem to happen in 'threes'...
Me: You'll jinx it! SHUT UP!!@#%

So we spazzed over that for a while, then I went online, and now I'm typing this. So yeah.

Yesterday my brother, sis-in-law, and their kids came over. The kids are uber-cute, but Riley's so ENERGETIC OMG. It's hard to bear with him. I'm not so great with kids. Can't stand 'em.

But yeah. I saw the tape of my play again. I miss it. A lot.
And I talked with my sis-in-law, Kathy. Like FRIENDS. It's a first.

So yeah. Hi.

Well, Sara picked me up for teen night. I gt in the car and the first thing I see is...a turtle?!@ Wtf was she doing with a turtle?!@$ Well, apparently she found it on the road and swerved to avoid it. It was a pretty male painted one, too. So first we went down to the river (in our flouncy skirts XD we must've looked like idiots) to put Mr. Turtle back in his natural habitat (he seemed very happy) and then we went to Teen Night. Well, we played pinball, confessed to each other that we sucked at pool, and played this shooting game. I lost, but my aiminy was more accurate. X3! Then we tried dancing and apparently I glowed under the blacklight. Oops. Well, we got non-alchoholic strawberry margaritas (mmmm :9) and went to play this game thing in the corner. It was fun and we got high scores and stuff. Eventually we danced some more. 

The bad parts: These asshole guys came up and started dancing (like, grinding) next to us. Sara and I have a name for it: Dance rape. >.>;
Logan stared at me, like, the whole time. Creeeeeepy.

So yeah. And today I drove. Woo-hoo.

Wow. I haven't updted in a while, have I? Well, Not much has happened, 'cept I got my temporary liscence and stuffs. I'm kind of angsty-bitchy due to cramps and stuff. :E But yeah. I might go to Teen Night tonight if my parents'll let me stay till a reasonable time. :/
I need rp. Now. Rargh.

Last night was so fun! Anna told me to go to Teen night at the bar, so O went with her, and it was too fun. Strawberry fizz drinks taste good, and it was just so awesome. I met a lot of new people. I plan on going again.

And it's weird, because Anna just started talking to me again. She's a 'popular' kid, and I went with her, basically on a covert mission, until I could find what was making her all friendly towards me. Well, there isn't anything attached. From what I know, she's just trying to be my friend and fit me in. And she's really nice, so I don't think it's a problem as long as I remember that I have other friends, too, and hang out with all of them.

Well, I didn't get much accomplished so far today. I'm SO BORED. I'd call someone, but Megan's not home, I was with Sara and Danielle yesterday, and I don't quite trust Anna. >.>;

But omg, HBP comes out sunday #$%%^&^

Well, my dad's started teaching me to drive. It's alright, I suppose. I'm just scared half to death of ever actually going on the road because of the horrible tapes they show me in driver's ed. 
But today was the last day of driver's ed. for the week. I talked to my brother on the phone, and he helped me soooo much. He gave me great advice and assurance. I'm just crying a lot today, for no particular reason. It sucks.

Well, my mom's almost done painting the living room. The whole house smells like fresh paint. Ew.

I need to draw something, but I'm not sure what. I also want to roleplayyyyy. :x

Sara and Danielle might come over later. Which is good, because it will take my mind off of driving. Actually, I might just ask my dad if he'll take me out for, like, 10 minutes to drive around. I need to get this stuff in my head.

Well, yesterday was fun. I went to this fl-in breakfast at an EAA chapter near my town, and Sara was there, in all of her blonde glory. XD So we looked at all the cute little airplanes. Then we went back and talked to my relatives that were there, and Sara went with us to a garage sale (there were some interesting magnets there) and another EAA chapter, where I had lunch, and there was an air show. 

Well, we could only stand sitting watching these airplanes for so long, so we went home, Sara got her car, and she and I went to Family Video to rent movies. I'm kind of a closet movie geek. XD So then Sara's mom meets us there (o.o;) and we go to Markmans because they're having a closeout sale. There was this really pretty dress, but it didn't fit right on me. :< But I did get a shirt that Sara picked out for me. 

So we get home and start Monty Python's The Meaning of Life. Wow, was that dumb. XD It was funny but embarrassing, so we turned it off and put Patch Adams in after dinner. OMFG, great movie. We watched The Calling, too. That movie's really good! And them we watched TV until eleven, when Sara had to go home, and I went to bed.  

Fun times, fun times. <3

Well, I'm in a rather good mood today, despite the fact that I'm running on 5 hours of sleep. Yesterday was a good day. I had Meg over for a while. We DDR'd and sang along with Wicked, and just talked.  Then, at *:00, Danielle spontaneously calls and asks if she and Sara can come over 'really quick'. I'm all "Wtf, alright..." So they do, and. OMG.

Sara is a BLONDE. Well, Strawberry blonde, actually, but still. 

And it looks GOOD on her! Too bad she only bleached her once brown hair so she can dye it purple later. XD

But yeah. So then we took a mini road trip around town to try and find Katrina, so Sara could show her the new hair color. We never did find her. 
XD Oh well, she'll see it in pictures. And Sara totally has the 'blonde act' down. It's funny.

Well, my closet's done, for the most part. I just got finished reading two books. XD I'm really bored. So yeah. Not much to say today. I volunteered a little at the library today, just to waste time, really. And right now my friends on AIM are either idle, away, or offline. x.o;

So I've got nothin'. XD

Well, here's an update for the past couple of days.

Sunday: Had Sara and Danielle over. Played Melee and stuff. It was fun, as usual. Nothing special. 

Monday (today): Cleaned out my closet. I found stuff I didn't even know I HAD in there. It was horrible. Memories from childhood that I had to pack away (like my American Girl dolls -sniff-) to make room for new stuff. Plus, I had to throw stuff all over my room in order to make room. I felt almost claustrophobic. I can't STAND messes. Oh, it was so incredibly terrible. But my mom pushed me to keep going, so I did. Well, I climbed up on a chair to get to the top of my shelves in there, and hit my head. So I'm crying and laughing at the same time, and then I hit my head AGAIN. Oh my GOD. I think I was about to burst with emotions then XD But I finally got it finished and stuff. So yeah.

Wow. This has been WEEK FROM HELL! I'll recap the days for ya.

Thursday: Nothing, really. Band, then sat on the computer until 6:00, when Megs came over. We talked about Erik. I think I might have cried a little. I was a tad depressed the rest of the night. We didn't fight. I'm glad she's there for me, but...yeah.

Friday: OMG HECTIC. I went to Driver's Ed. I sat on a plastic stool in the commons for 4 HOURS. My God, did the bone in my butt hurt after that. x.o; Ow. Then marching practice! That helped. Sara and I made up, and I came over to her house for a bit. I was just randomly depressed that day, but Danielle cheered me up. Then, after Melee, we went to the rodeo! :B And I got a cowboy hat. Because I'm a dork. Plus, I seem to end up going every year anyway and I felt out of place. XD

Saturday(today): I'm so tired. Marching really takes a lot out of you. Stupid 3-mile march. x.o; Then Erik, Meg, Ashley, Sara and I went to the gas station and Erik got us juice and water and stuff. The conversation we had was kind of funny.

Me:I don't have any money. Erik:I'll pay. Me:You sure? Erik:Yes. Me:But then I'll feel guilty! Erik:Don't feel guilty, just buy me a soda later!

And then I sat and watched the parade with Sara, and then I went to Bud's house for out usual family gathering and stuff. I must have smelled wonderful. XD Mmm, dried-sweaty band geek. I packed up my flute, ate, and watched TV with Katrina for a looong time, then we walked home. And then I took a much-needed shower. XD

So yeah. I'mma go fall over now.

Well, after band practice (sara-free) and dog-washing, I got to see my Megz0rs today. <3 Meg is my closest same-grade friend. When me, Meg, Holly, and Ashley are in the same room, we're nearly inseperable.

So, We talked, listened to Wicked, DDR'd, and I told her about my months-long crush on Erik. There's a song from Wicked that goes with it. I ever cried a little. And I showed her a really cute picture I drew of him as the Phantom and me as Christine. X'D And she was awesome and supportive and stuff. So that's good.

So yeah.

Well, I raked grass and weeds, and my parents trimmed bushes. OMG, on this one bush, there was a vine and it was plotting world domination, I swear! It was huge! Once my parents wrestled it out of the ground, I tried to pick the thing up to put it in the pit. Well, this is no ordinary, run-of-the-mill vine This vine was probably 3 times my size. We're talking about a 15 or so foot vine. XD So eventually I give up and drag it to the pit. X3

So yeah. That's been my day so far. But still. Mastermind vines! Aahhhh!

-flees!-

Ragh, I'm in angsty ranting mode, I'm not sure why. Maybe it's because I don't want to go home tomorrow and I have to anyway, because I have marching band practice and driver's ed-gagchokedie- next week.

And to think, 10 minutes ago I was having giggle fits that I couldn't control. 

I love it here in Chicago. I wanted to see...him...while I was here, but I couldn't. And chances are I won't be back till August (and I'll probably have to drive here -.-;) when everything ends. 

I have Evanescence in my head. Greeaat.

And tomorrow I have to go with my mom to my Gramps and Grandma Sue's house for dinner. My Aunt Tammy might be there, she might not be. If she is, I really, really hope she's not drunk. Reminds me of when I went to her house for Christmas once, she had a little too much to drink, and she got violent. Aunt Tammy's definitely an angry drunk. I ended up crying in my mother's arms while I was there. It wasn't very fun.

Well, today I had fun. Amy and Marty came over to Lolo's and we swam, then Amy went home and we watched a movie. Peter made a couple of (annoying) phone calls, and from what I heard, David wanted to come but went with his dad to a movie instead.

Oh, I never really got much of an answer from him, either. >.>; Oh well.

Time to go upstairs and listen to music.

Agh, I'm gonna burst with anticipation if he doesn't get online soon ><; ...Sorry I keep rambling, I'm filling up your friends' pages with nonsense, but I have to get this out, it's driving me insane! I finally ask him, then my phone company DISCONNECTS THE SERVER and doesn't notify us. So we have to wait till today to call and ask WTF HAPPENED XD

Eeeeeee$#%$^& -hops around-

And I'm also a -little- jealous of someone, but I can't say who, as they read my LJ. And I don't want them to find out. >.>;

-flees!-

Well, after 2 and a half days of no computer, I am back!
Now for a recap of what happened during the week.

Saturday:
Went to my brother's house to babysit my niece, Alex, and nephew, Riley. Alex is a year old, and Riley is almost three. They're so cute! You can't understand what they're saying most of the time, and Alex should start speaking words soon. Right now it's just baby babble, but she'll get there. 

Sunday:
Went to Wal-Mart and got stuff, then came home and I frantically tried to get on the internet. I failed miserably. XD

Monday (today!):
Eh, went to Wal-Mart again and got food. I'm going back to Chicago tomorrow, so if I'm not on, that's why. I'm anxiously awaiting his answer...if he ever comes on. x.o;

Okay. I asked him out. Mission accomplished (kind of).

...Now what? I just wait for him to give me an answer? 
Is he -going- to give me an answer?

Well, I'll give him 'till Sunday to respond to me. If he doesn't I'll ask him (probably through someone) what his answer is. 

Gah. The anticipation sucks. Chances are I asked too soo and he'll say no. Hahaha, I probably couldn't have timed this any worse, actually. Then again, it won't be the first time a guy said no to that question, and it won't be nearly as bad as my last let-down, so I shoudln't be too shocked.

...Sorry. I'm rambling again.
I'm done now.

Ok, my day so far went like this:

Got up, took a shower, went online. Then I ate and went to the library and got a job volunteering there for the summer. (On the 28th, I get to go down there and help set up for a lunch with the rodeo queen! XD -brick'd-) Then I got back home, mowed the lawn (that lawnmower freaks me out a little...) and went online. HE was online. I asked him out. He has yet to respond. -dead-

And i talked to Gramma Morrison for less than 5 minutes. IT'S A MIIIIRACLE!

...XD 

-spazzdie-

Well, I now realise how fragile human life is. A student from my high school, Kelly, has been killed in a car crash. I don't know if he was drunk or what happened when he crashed. He was in my health class for a while. 

I didn't really like him, but it's just...disturbing.

Yes indeed, time to sit around and do nothing all day. Yay! <3

And it's only 12:37. Wow. XD

I should call someone or something. Hmm...Eh, nah. I'll figure out something to do later.

Well, I'm back home now, but I am -so- tired. I couldn't sleep at all last night, too many thoughts swirling around in my head. I hate that. I think that's the most partying I've done, ever. XD Oh well. 

But it was fun. And I think I actually got a little tan! And my face is being devoured by freckles. X3

But yeah. I'll most likely be on more often now that I'm home.

<3 to all!

Well, after we walked down to the school and met up w/ Lauren and Peter, we all met back at Lolo's house for swimming! OMGS funnn! Well, except that Meg kept scratching Peter and Lauren bit him, so now he looks like he's been mauled by a grizzly bear... But the dunking and splashing and funnn!

And then we took a break to eat chips with peanut butter and talk. And then more swimming!

AND THEN I GOT FRIED. 

OMG sunburn sucks so much ;3; it huuurts.

But yeah. Peter and I are better friends now yey. And stuff. 

But then people, who I will not name, decide to skinny dip o.o; EEEW.

'Kay. I'm done now.

Well, after sitting around waiting what seemed like for-ev-er for Lolo's 8th grade grad. ceremony to get here, it finally did. I got to watch my friends graduate, then we went out for ice cream! Man that was fun. Now I remember why I have such a crush on David <333 XD

But yeah. I hope I get to see them again before I go home, whenever that is.

Well, today was entertaining. My bro and I truly are country hicks.

"Ooh, look, you can see Chicago from this here window!"

"OMG LOOK A HELICOPTER"

...And then I run over to peer out the blinds of the hospital with my brother (a grown man XD) and stuff. 

But tomorrow I have to swim. In front of BOYS. IN A BIKINI. 

Why didn't I just get a sensible one piece like usual? ;o;

stupid stomach.

Yep, I am indeed. My grandpa, who lives in Illinois, is sick in the intensive care unit in Christ Hospital so I'm sitting at my cousin's house typing this. Yay for 3 computers in the house? XD 

Mrrr. I sort of have a crush on this one kid again. I think I'm gonna see him Tuesday. X3!

Gah. Marchins isn't fun. Sitting in the sun in hot uniforms isn't either. With horrible, horrible hats. And arm lyres that cut off the circulation to your ARM.
And I have sunburn and freckles on my face, and freckles on my hands.
But we got soda.
And stuff.

But I got in trouble for not telling my friend when an audition for a play was when she asked me. Then I got in trouble for lying. Now I don't think my dad trusts me anymore. 

Ragh. I feel like breaking something.

Had Sara and Danielle come over today. We played some melee, rented Mario Party 6 and WarioWare((omg most awesome game EVAR I MUST BUY IT$#^%$)) I like Mona the best X3, and those two little girls. XD Omg funfun game.

But yeah. Haven't updated in a while. I have major marching tomorrow. Gah. >.o; I also have stoodying to doooo. But I get to see Erik so it's all worth it. 

...4 school days left. How utterly depressing.

I think I'm getting sick. My throat is all hurt-y and stuff. :/ I can't sing to my soundtracks! ;o;

Hahaha, but good news- Erik and I really are friends now! He gave me a picture of him in his track uniform. <3! X3 And stuff.

I went shopping and bought nothing, but issk, more money for later!

I need to draw something, or ink this one thing. Mrr.

Gah. I'm just kind of depressed. Squi, Lolo, and David aren't on, but at least I have Ana to talk to. <3 I found song lyrics that describe my dilemma with Meg and Erik perfectly. I'm still obsessing over him. ><;

Now for the lyrics.

 

Hands touch, eyes meet
Sudden silence, sudden heat
Hearts leap in a giddy whirl
He could be that boy
But I'm not that girl:

Don't dream too far
Don't lose sight of who you are
Don't remember that rush of joy
He could be that boy
I'm not that girl

Ev'ry so often we long to steal
To the land of what-might-have-been
But that doesn't soften the ache we feel
When reality sets back in

Blithe smile, lithe limb
She who's winsome, she wins him
Gold hair with a gentle curl
That's the girl he chose
And Heaven knows
I'm not that girl:

Don't wish, don't start
Wishing only wounds the heart
I wasn't born for the rose and the pearl
There's a girl I know
He loves her so
I'm not that girl:

The only part that isn't right is that Megan's hair is blonde (gold), but not curly. It's stick-straight. XD

<3<3?

School was fun today. Erik, Hanna, Dani, Jessica and I had a sort of chalk fight in the band room. I'm starting to dislike Hanna a little. :/ And then there's the whole Erik thing....yeah, not even gonna get into that. But yeah. And Tammy's birthday was today! So that's good. But yeah. We get yearbooks on Friday. It depresses me a little. :/ This school year was wonderful, I don't want it to end! -brick'd-

Man, am I gonna be sad when the seniors leave. No more Dawn, no Kristy, no Ashley or Jessica, no Ric or Darryl....Man, it's gonna be quiet in the school. :/

 

And now...

Yeah. Saturday was Solo-ensemble. I was in one thing- Polka Band, of all things. XD -brick'd- But it was still fun. I got to flounce around in a pretty short ruffly skirt and look cute! And that's always a plus right there. Let's see. I got there and followed Sara around for a bit, ate a snack with her, then we went back to the 'homeroom', this huuuge gym where many a band/choir nerd was camped out, playing/singing, listening to music, or sleeping. Sara and I decided to play cards for a while. Egyptian Rattail is a fun game. X3 It's really long, though. Then she went to change for her Broadway solo and I waited. And waited. AND WAITED. I went to go look for her and we ran into each other and I halped her practice and stuff. After I watched her broadway solo, Dawn's broadway solo, and Sara's regular solo, I was ready for FOOD. So I went outside where they were cooking stuff on a grill in my big red comfy sweatshirt and teeny skirt XD and waited in a HUGE line. Well, when I was about halfway through the line, Dawn and her mom saw me and she ran over to me and stuff and eventually she was all "Can I cut in line? Will anyone mind?" and I let her because I'm nice :3 So we talked, and I held my skirt so it didn't fly up because of the wind and stuff, and we got food and went inside to sit down by Katrina, her mom and dad, Mrs. Suehs, and her daughter. We talked about lots of stuff. It was fun. And then polka band did alright...we got a second place, but oh well.

Yep, you guessed it, today I went to a super-cool poetry slam today. It was really fun! First I did this poetry workshop thing. I had a poem with. We watched videos and talked and ate and learned. It was so fun! Then the slam came.

All the teachers were all "READ YOUR STUFF, SIGN UP, SIGHN UP RAAARHGHR!" XD
But in order to actually compete for prizes, you had to have TWO poems, not one. I had one. I don't write a lot of poetry. So they let me read my poem 'to warm the judges up', which is fine. i just wanted people to hear my poem, not to win prizes. I got a good score, too! And I was first, so I set the mood for the night. :3

This is an annual thing. Imma write some stuff for next year. <3!
(Oh, and a cute guy sat next to me! :D)

GAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHRARARGH. >:(

 

Well, I finally realized that, though Meg has divorced parents and stuff, her social life incredibly makes up for it. She has the -perfect- example of a boyfriend, another really good guy friend (she's gonna break perfect boyfriend's heart if he ever finds out she likes her guy friend) and all kinds of other friends. She's outgoing and stuff, too. Not to mention she's got a great voice and can act really well. And che can do really good crafts. And is pretty.

It -pisses me off-. Yes. I'm jealous. So sue me.

Me, I'm the total opposite. I have enough (girl) friends. And Sara is the best friend I could ask for. But guy friends? Pfft. Guys like to either pretend I don't exist, make comments at me, and sometimes tease me. I'm not sure why. I have 3 crushes. The strongest is on Travis. He's a junior, but guess what? Oh, look, he doesn't notice that I exist anymore after the play. Ric is my 2nd strongest. He's really, -really- cute and stuff, a little arrogant, but hey, so am I. (He also pays no attention to me.) The 3rd is on David, who is a year younger than me, a bit of an airhead, and lives in another freakin' state. And I have no idea how to approach ANY OF THEM (except David, no prob there except of the fact we live in dif. states.) All my guy friends are in Illinois. Another best friend (and fave cousin) is in Illinois.

Now. I went to the dentist today only to find out they can't do anything to my retainer to make it -not- make me gag. So what, am I supposed to choke on it, or what?!

And another thing. I'm having such PROBLEMS with food. If I didn't love food so much, I swear I'd become anorexic. Man, life sucks right now.

I know I have all the stuff in the world to be proud of, and to be grateful for, and I am. But I can't help wondering about some of this other stuff.

OMG so happy hyper wheeeeeeeeeee! XD Hahaha. It's great.

But yeah. Had -uber-bad cramps. I mean, so bad I couldn't sit still. I was running around the house like an idiot. XD My mom let me stay home for a while. I took a nap, then they went away, but I was totally drained until swing choir. Then OMG SPAZZ HYPER HAPPY WTF!!!!11oneeleventyseven!!@#

Hahaha, I'll stop now. Anyway, read some uber-cool poems, did this assignment on one of them. It's by Robert Frost and it's really neato. <3

Swing choir: YAY! I got to dance and act so stupid and stuff in front of my crush, who, I -think-, was watching. Hahaha. XD <3! Yay for cuteness! I was all "Wheeee~!<3<3!" And now I'm still really hyper. I had cake! And roleplayed with two uber-awesome people. ((P.S., if you look at this, Hi Shannon! :D)) But yeah. <3!

Love to all! <3<3<3
